HEADWORD: Recommission
<hw>Re`com*mis"sion</hw> <pr>(r?`k?m*m?sh?n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<def>To commission again; to give a new commission to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Officers whose time of service had expired were to be
<qex>recommissioned</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Marshall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recommit</ent>⟦br⟧
